# AI features in B2C PMES

## Architecture

- **Gemini is the default implementation**, but code is split by **interface** (`backend/src/ai/interfaces/`) and **providers** (`gemini-tts`, `noop`) so another vendor can be added without rewriting the app module.
- **Never put API keys in the frontend.** TTS goes `browser → POST /ai/tts → Nest → Gemini`. The client only sets `VITE_API_BASE_URL`.
- **Cost control:** `AI_PROVIDER=noop` disables paid calls (503 on TTS). Server-side **in-memory cache** dedupes identical text+voice (see `AiService`). Tighten further with rate limits or Redis later.

## Developer workflow (Cursor)

- When changing Ka-uban behavior, edit **server** prompts in `gemini-tts.provider.ts` (single place) rather than duplicating in the client.
- To add a **new** capability (e.g. chat): add a DTO, controller route, and a new provider or method behind the same `AiModule` pattern; keep responses small and validated.
- Ask for product guardrails: max body size, PII in prompts, and fallbacks when AI is disabled.

## Environment quick reference

| Variable | Role |
|----------|------|
| `AI_PROVIDER` | `noop` \| `gemini` \| `openai` \| `grok` (xAI Grok TTS) |
| `GEMINI_API_KEY` | Required if `gemini` |
| `OPENAI_API_KEY` | Required if `openai` (OpenAI `audio/speech`, MP3) |
| `XAI_API_KEY` | Required if `grok` (`POST https://api.x.ai/v1/tts`, MP3) |
| `GEMINI_TTS_MODEL` / `OPENAI_TTS_MODEL` | Optional model overrides |
| `VITE_API_BASE_URL` | Frontend → Nest (e.g. `http://localhost:3000`) |

Voice names: **Gemini** uses names like `Aoede`. **OpenAI** accepts `alloy`, `echo`, `fable`, `onyx`, `nova`, `shimmer` (unknown names map to `nova`). **Grok** accepts `eve`, `ara`, `leo`, `rex`, `sal` (unknown → `ara`).
